<item>
            <title>[LU-3793] conf-sanity, subtest test_66 fails due to previous state</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3793</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Nathaniel Clark &amp;lt;nathaniel.l.clark@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/effa4886-0980-11e3-901c-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/effa4886-0980-11e3-901c-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_66 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MDT start failed&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: conf-sanity 66&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If test_61 fails (a la &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3792&quot; title=&quot;Failure conf-sanity, test_61, error: getxattr failed: -61&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3792&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3792&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) then the state is left partially up, and the setup call in 66 will fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="20505">LU-3793</key>
