                            <comment id="260855" author="adilger" created="Thu, 9 Jan 2020 07:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close old bug&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64756" author="adilger" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2013 16:53:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The goal of this ticket should be to make conf-sanity more robust about resetting the state in the face of failures.  Unfortunately, this should take a lower priority than actually fixing the real test failures, since we can never land a patch that has any failures, and ideally we would never see failures and this issue would be moot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
